[1] Cholera - Kenya (Nakuru County)
Date: Tue 28 Apr 2015
Source: AllAfrica, The Star report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504281302.html


Four people have died in Nakuru [County] in a suspected cholera outbreak at Ponda Mali estate; 9 others are at the Nakuru Referral Hospital.

Nakuru Health executive Mungai Kabii said the 1st case was reported last week on Wednesday, 22 Apr 2015. "We have 6 people from Rhonda area, 2 from Bondeni and 1 from Ponda Mali currently undergoing treatment," Kabii said in Nakuru town yesterday, 27 Apr 2015.

He said the county has started an anti-cholera drive to educate residents on the disease. "We have banned all street food vendors. It is unfortunate that we have lost 4 people in a week," Kabii said.

The county has started issuing chlorine tablets to residents.

[Byline: Joyce Kimani]

