[The city of Nakuru is the capital of Nakuru County in Kenya and former capital of the Rift Valley Province. Nakuru County is in southwestern Kenya and can be seen on a map at: http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kenya_counties_map_Labelled.jpg. - Mod.LL]

******
[2] Cholera - Nigeria (Delta State)
Date: Mon 20 Apr 2015
Source: Business Standard [edited]
http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/cholera-claims-30-lives-in-nigeria-115042001326_1.html


At least 30 people have been killed in the latest cholera outbreak in Nigeria's oil-rich Delta state's Isoko South community, a health official said on Monday [20 Apr 2015].

According to the official, people of the local community had been facing challenges of cholera disease since 2010, when their main source of drinking water was polluted. He said, rather than seeking medical help at the local health center, the people resorted to traditional medicines and self-medication to cure themselves.

"It was not until after the disease had claimed 5 lives that they (the local residents) brought it to the knowledge of the local authorities," the official said.

In 2010, more than 30 people had died when the 1st cholera outbreak was recorded following the pollution of the main source of water supply in the same area of Delta state.

--
